Nigeria's Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, has ordered the posting of three new commissioners of police to Imo, Plateau and Adamawa states. The postings, which was announced on Tuesday, is with immediate effect, according to Frank Mba, Force Public Relations Officer. 



